[Scene 1 | 0–4s]
"How does an AI read an entire sentence... all at once?"

[Scene 2 | 4–9s]
"It uses something called Attention — but not just once. It does it multiple times, simultaneously."

[Scene 3 | 9–15s]
"Imagine a sentence: 'The cat sat on the mat.' Each word looks at every other word and asks — how much do I care about you?"

[Scene 4 | 15–20s]
"That's one attention head. But Multi-Head Attention runs eight of these in parallel — each one focusing on different relationships."

[Scene 5 | 20–26s]
"One head tracks grammar. Another tracks meaning. Another tracks position. They all learn different patterns."

[Scene 6 | 26–32s]
"Then all their outputs are concatenated and projected into one powerful representation."

[Scene 7 | 32–37s]
"That's why Transformers are so powerful. Multiple perspectives. One unified understanding."

